rows.title: Introduction
rows.titleText:
Welcome to the Omnitrix Choose Your Own Adventure! This CYOA is intended to be a crossover with other franchises, but it can still be enjoyed as a standalone adventure.

You have been transported to another universe, whether by Celestialsapiens, ROB, Professor Paradox, or some other means. Fortunately, you possess an Omnitrix specifically created for your survival to wherever in the omniverse you find youself in. The Omnitrix is an alien device that can transform you into various aliens with unique abilities and weaknesses. It serves as a genetic library for alien DNA, containing millions of samples that can potentially be unlocked for use.

Now, with the Omnitrix, you embark on a thrilling adventure set in another universe. You will encounter and meet your favorite characters

Throughout this CYOA, you will utilize Omnitrix points to unlock various features, upgrades, and alterations for your Omnitrix. Additionally, Physical points will allow you to enhance your body, physical abilities, DNA, and even adjust your age, and more non releated things.

objects.title: Azmuth's Omnitrix origins
objects.text: In another universe, Azmuth created an Omnitrix. However, due to an incident, he had no choice but to send it to another universe (or to a location in his universe if you picked standalone), a Celestialsapien or Paradox found it and gave it to you or by sheer luck found you. it is unknown if Azmuth survived or not.

objects.title: Creator Searching
objects.text: (Only if you took Azmuth's Omnitrix origin) Remember Azmuth? well not only is that Azmuth alive but he is actively looking in the omniverse for the Omnitrix, and when he comes he will judge if you are worthy or not. This Azmuth actually has a family with his wife Zennith and has children, which give him all the more reason if any to find you and take you Omnitrix if necessary so he can sleep soundly at night knowing the one thing that brought Zennith back his life is not used as a weapon.

objects.title: Ben-less
objects.text: The good news is there is no variant of Ben Tennyson, meaning you are the only one with an Omnitrix, the bad news is there is no Ben 10 to save the world from canon events, mentor you, or help you out. Good luck!

objects.title: Hero team up!
objects.text: Ben 10 will meet you, this encounter is inevitable, even if you picked to go to another universe with no Ben 10 mix-in, then Ben will accidentally or purposefully travel to this universe, and may or may not stay depending on his circumstances. Be careful you're not evil, this may not be Ben prime but he still probably has more aliens than you.

objects.title: Your Own Rival (Kevin)
objects.text: You got yourself a rival at your hands, it your own version of Kevin Levin, though in the metaphorical sense as you and him/her will meet one day and become enemies.

objects.title: Musical theme
objects.text: You have a soundtrack that automatically plays whoever or whenever you are fighting that you can turn on and off.

rows.title: Franchise
rows.titleText: This section is where you picked whether this be a standalone or crossover.

objects.title: Just omniversee
objects.text: you are taken to a version of the ben 10  universe, nothing else, nothing more.

objects.title: Crossover in the omniversee
objects.text:
The universe your sent to is a mix between the Ben 10 universe and another franchise.
you now entered a mix of ben 10 and the universe you are in, this changes canon in different ways.

objects.title: Isekai into franchise
objects.text: The only thing Ben 10 related is the Omnitrix, the universe you picking will be of a different franchise in no relation to Ben 10 at all.

objects.title: Earth Unaware
objects.text: Earth is mostly if not completely unaware of the wider universe, the Plumbers (if any) on earth are all retired, all factions or people not original associated with aliens don't know of alien existence. This is useful if you picked a universe where you need or want the element of surprise and factions not knowing your aliens weaknesses.

objects.title: Hiding Aliens
objects.text: Alien life exist, but instead of looking up, it near us. Aliens live on earth in secrets from the rest of humanity

objects.title: alien defence force
objects.text: Earth has prepared for alien, creating the ADF for capturing and even killing aliens if needed as this secrets forces is worldwide in its quest to safeguard earth.

objects.title: The Darker Turn
objects.text:
All events from whatever universe you sent into that has horrifying implication that get blushed off will not but instead get fleshed out the more you explore the world as everything gets generally darker.
This may affect canon and make main characters suffer more if possible.

objects.title: Osmosian
objects.text: You are halve Osmosians, you can channel absorbed energy or materials, and you can live up to hundreds of years, but keep in mind the problems of getting addicted when absorbing energy.

objects.title: human
objects.text: You are a plain old human, with no abilities at all, The good news is your DNA will show up as normal if not slightly strange altered by the Omnitrix but not enough to be noticeable without the right technology, The bad news is that you have no powers.

objects.title: Anodite
objects.text: You are halve Anodite, a free-spirited species of humanoid energy beings who derived their life-force from mana, meaning you now have the spark of magic. depending on what universe you picked you may become even more powerful than canon due to the surrounding mana

objects.title: reincarnation
objects.text:
You sent to this universe via reincarnation, you still remember everything if you want or forget until you encounter the Omnitrix.
Your Omnitrix will arrive when you 10 or at the age you want to decide on.

objects.title: Drop-In (Isekai)
objects.text:
You are sent to this new universe, the good news is you don't wait for this, the bad news is you have no identity, and no family but you get a lot of points and are sent to a safe unmonitored location, safety may vary depending on the best spot for you to appear without attracting attention.
For example, if you pick Raildex, you are sent to School District 10 due to how unmonitored it is

objects.title: Backstory Of The Century
objects.text: Good news you have a created backstory as to your own existence in the universe you picked and why you are here, and there is evidence to back it up, be lucky that whoever did this did it for you. PS may or may not alter reality and may vary from fantastical like being taken by aliens one day, to normal

objects.title: Rated For 10 And Up
objects.text: You get to pick your age, whether that be sent into that universe isekai style and turned into whatever age you pick to being that chosen age when you get the Omnitrix if you picked reincarnation.

rows.title: Omnitrix features
rows.titleText: This section is where you can get the chosen Omnitrix's features, extensions, and upgrades, at the get-go, ready and unlocked for you to use at your own discretion.

objects.title: Basic Omnitrix Knowledge
objects.text: Your Omnitrix has successfully downloaded essential information and settings in addition to transformation capabilities. These include GPS, maps, communication functions, and rebooting options. However, you do not possess Knowledge of advanced features such as master control or non-canon features like a USB adapter.

objects.title: Repair DNA
objects.text:
Not only can your Omnitrix repair DNA damage from people but can also cure cancer, genetic diseases, optimize the DNA's immune system, and restore a person lifespan if genetical possible.
wait... all this for 1 omni points? that crazy, better exploit it while you can if it ever gets fixed!

objects.title: Energy Feedback Loop Blasts
objects.text:
Your Omnitrix is set to shoot out an 360 degree Energy Feedback Loop Blast when someone forcibly tries to remove it by a dangerous amount of force or in a hostile manner. 

Useful if for getting rid of pesky thieves looking to steal your Omnitrix

objects.title: Recalibrated
objects.text: Your Omnitrix has been recalibrated. It will adjust to your biometrics and preferences once you use it for the first time. expect a slight time delay of a few minutes during this adjustment process as your watch updates itself with random features and no miss transformations.

objects.title: USB Detected
objects.text: Your Omnitrix possesses the capability to generate a universal USB cable that can seamlessly connect with various technologies. This enables you to hack systems, obtain data, interact with machines, charge electronic devices, and even analyze unfamiliar substances.

objects.title: Bioscan
objects.text: The Omnitrix not only scans DNA but also has the ability to scan for diseases, injuries, and can utilize various scanning methods such as infrared, ultrasound, x-ray, and more

objects.title: Master Control
objects.text: You now have access to master control, allowing you to transform into any alien. However, having access to everything does not guarantee that you know how to activate them correctly.

objects.title: Thought Shield
objects.text: Unlike other Omnitrices, yours can protect the user from being mind-controlled. However, it cannot prevent others from reading your surface thoughts.

objects.title: Omnitrix To The Rescue l
objects.text: Omnitrix to the rescure (-3 Omni Points for l, -5 for ll, -8 for lll) The Omnitrix recharges automatically when you are in physical danger, about to be possessed, have a hostile parasite, about to die.

objects.title: Omnitrix To The Rescue ll
objects.text: Depending on the threat your Omnitrix either automatically recharge or will automatically transform you into an alien best suited to survive whatever is about to kill you, possesses you, or previous circumstances mentioned in Omnitrix To The Rescue l but this is limited to the aliens you already have in your playlist

objects.title: Omnitrix To The Rescue lll
objects.text: Depending on the danger or situation, your omnitrix will, either instantly recharge, turn you into an alien on your playlist, or potentially unlock a new alien suited for the situation if deemed necessary by the circumstances.

objects.title: DNA Database
objects.text: Your Omnitrix has a catalogue of information, weaknesses, and medical files on your aliens to use whenever you want, it even has files on human medical treatment.

objects.title: Unlockable With A Touch
objects.text: Good news, you can temporarily access aliens not present in the active playlist just by pulling up the Omnitex faceplate. creating a holographic touchpad where you can use specific patterns to temporarily unlock new aliens, of coruse these are random with no control over what you get. these temporly transformation last only one transformation so becaful

objects.title: Ultimatrix
objects.text: Your Omnitrix is actually an Ultimatrix, capable of evolving your alien to their ultimate form by placing the selected transformation in a simulation of the "worst-case scenario" bad news is you can't access the ultimatix feature at all due to lack of knowledge, and even if you use it then its going to be a drain on its power.

objects.title: T.A.P
objects.text: You have access to TAP, a way to enter the Omnitrix with whatever you have on you, useful for storing items or simple exploring the omnitrix, you can also do maintainance.

objects.title: Omni-Kix/Omni-Naut Armor
objects.text: Great news you have the Omnitrix key, inserted it and you get both Omni-Kix and Omni-Naut Armor, enhancing your transformations power at the cost of drawing more power from the Omnitrix

objects.title: Magic proof
objects.text: Your Omnitrix has some Mana based safeguards against magic, be that possession, spells directed for both the user and omnitrix, or anything really, but that doesn't mean its foolproof

objects.title: reverse hacking
objects.text: someone trying to hack your Omnitrix? they get reverse hacked by your Omnitix instead

objects.title: Omni compatible
objects.text: Your Omnitrix is compatible with many technologies, meaning that you can incorporate other tech into the omnitrix like a drafw star  or sonic screwdriver.

objects.title: Omni Shield
objects.text: You Omnitrix comes with  in built forces field system that continuous able to project around you but drains the Omnitrix power supple and doesn't allow transformation while in use.

rows.title: Alien Transformations
rows.titleText: This is section is about how the Omnitrix's aliens forms.

objects.title: Random 10
objects.text: You get 10 random aliens for your set of 10.

objects.title: Picking 10
objects.text: You get to pick 10 aliens of your choice

objects.title: 5 Year Later Aliens
objects.text: Your Omnitrix has the DNA samples of all the 5 year later aliens, they are not unlocked but there and may be available in your starter set.

objects.title: Interfranchise Extraterrestrials
objects.text: Your Omnitrix has the DNA samples of aliens from other franchise like Time Lords, Weeping Angels, Klyntars and more, but are not set in your set of 10 and must be unlocked.

objects.title: Alien Instincts
objects.text: When transformed you will gain the knowledge on how to use each alien form you transformed into.

objects.title: Regenerative Transformation
objects.text: Your aliens forms may take damage in battle but when transformed back to normal or into another alien, all injuries will disappear.

objects.title: Growing Up
objects.text: Whenever you transformed, your omnitrix will turn you into an adult version of the alien chosen regardless of age, making them stronger, faster, and very useful if your stuck in a child body.

objects.title: In Sickness To Health
objects.text: When you transform into an alien while ill, your Omnitrix will automatically eliminate any ailment you had in human form.

rows.title: AI
rows.titleText: This section is about the Omnitrix AI, you get to pick what upgrades your Omnitrix has in the form of AI.

objects.title: Silent Guardian
objects.text: Your Omnitrix cares about you, it views you as its master, its obedient to you only, the Omnitrix will always be there for you even if it can't talk, this allows your Omnitrix to act independently when needed like blasting out an energy pulse, refusing to be removed, activate on its own, move on its own back to you if severed. expect the omnitrix to feel extra tight when your feeling miserable.

objects.title: Watching Companion
objects.text: Your Omnitrix AI is alive, it has developed into an individual entity that can communicate with you, gaining a hardlight human form of the opposite gender, she/he can appear whenever they want, but can only stay around in that form for between six hours to one.

rows.title: Drawbacks
rows.titleText: Drawbacks are ways to boost your points at the cost of drawbacks on your Omnitrix that may negatively affect you in the long run.

objects.title: Slow Mode
objects.text: Your transformations take a few seconds to complete instead of being instant and there is no blinding flash of light, this usually comes as a freaky but quick transformation as seen in Alien Swarm movie, though this can be dangerous due to how long it takes to transform now.

objects.title: Limited Energy Reserves
objects.text: The Omnitrix has limited energy reserves, meaning that each transformation consumes a significant amount of power. You will need to carefully manage their transformations and plan accordingly to avoid running out of energy at crucial moments.

objects.title: Cooldown Period
objects.text: After transforming into an alien form, there is a cooldown period before the user can transform again. This drawback prevents you from constantly switching between forms.

objects.title: Damage Reboot
objects.text: Your Omnitrix will transform you back whenever you get hit with enough damage be it lethal, knocked out, defeated, hit hard enough.

objects.title: Electromagnetic Interference
objects.text: When the Omnitrix is exposed to strong electromagnetic interference, it may trigger unintentional transformations. It won't deactivate until the interference source is removed but can also work in reverse, causing the user to rapidly shift from one form to another until the electromagnetic interference  stopped by someone or something.

objects.title: Deleting Power Surge
objects.text: The Omnitrix can accidently delete its stored DNA samples of aliens if it endures a strong power surge. You could lose all your aliens if your Omnitrix is hit by multiple power surges, good news is that it is possible to recover them through reunlocking them.

objects.title: Random self Destruct
objects.text: There a random code and audio response that can activate the Omnitrix self destruct. Be careful of what you do or say from now on

objects.title: Access Is Hard
objects.text: There more difficulties to accessing the Omnitrix's setting then you thought, you really should get a manual for this thing because it isn't  that convenient.

objects.title: Template Mishap
objects.text:
There are bad news, the genetic template of the Omnitrx, the one supposed to transform you back to your own appearance has not been set and now you look like ben. 
So... this is how he felt like.

objects.title: Choice
objects.text: This is a Choice, and inside of it, you can place images and text. Scores can be added to it, and have Point-types attached. Addons can be added underneath the image and text. In the Functions at the bottom of the choice, there is an array of different things that can be done. Default text like this can be turned off in Features then Manage Defaults.

rows.title: Items
rows.titleText: Here in this section are items and tools you are able to bring with you alongside your adventure, they cost physical points instead of Omni Points.

objects.title: Proto-Tool
objects.text: The Proto-Tool is a high-tech multi-functional weapon, it is the most versatile tech in the known universe with a number of transformations, but it can be upgraded to have more modes. Be careful you don't kill yourself when using it.

objects.title: Potis Altiare piece
objects.text: You have a single piece of the Potis Altiare with you.

objects.title: Currency
objects.text: You get the selected amount of 8000 dollars reformatted into a currency that accepted wherever you are at.

objects.title: Bringing Your Stuff
objects.text: you can bring whatever you have to the universe you're sent into, whether that be a laptop, phone, or anything you can carry is fine.

objects.title: ID Mask
objects.text: ID Masks are a form of alien technology utilized to conceal the identity of the wearer.

objects.title: Horas At Your Service
objects.text: Horas is a series of robots created by the Plumbers, partly organic, it consistently maintains a cheerful and optimistic attitude in most situations. However, he can be easily frightened. He enjoys making jokes and considers himself quite humorous. with built-in teleportation technology based as Null Void projectors, flight, camouflage via attributes based on the primary dominant species in his vicinity and can reproduce asexually to spawn miniature drones connected wirelessly to exchange visuals and information. Horas is a good robot to have with you on  your travels if to investigate the surrounded, gather information, or even crack a joke, just be mindful that while your Omnitrix has the blueprints to create Horas' that they are fragile.

objects.title: Sonic Screwdriver
objects.text: You have a sonic screwdriver, able to do basically anything, in terms of scanning, opating machines, and much more

objects.title: franchise booklet
objects.text: You have a book of everything  about the franchise you going into, either as a book, or in your Omnitrix, which updates itself based on your world's internet.

rows.title: Physical
rows.titleText: this section will use physicals points to affect your own body, these may or may not also affect your transformations depending on it.

objects.title: Ideal self
objects.text: You are the Ideal version of yourself in both mind and body, partly due to the Omnitrix fixing up your body, all mental illness are gone and your body is at its peak in age regardless of what you do or eat.

objects.title: Bullet Timer
objects.text:
You fast enough to dodge bullets, whether it be from far away or in a fight, you can dodge them relatively with ease like a anime character, you just have to watch out for the bullets you can't see.

does not work on transformations that can easily dodge bullets

objects.title: Spider sense
objects.text:
You have the uncanny feeling when you about to get killed, this may come in feeling a sniper locked on to you, or an ambush. 

Does not work on transformations that already have enhances senses

objects.title: Must Be Your Lucky Day
objects.text:
You are lucky, very much so that when fliping a coin its usually lands on what side you choose. 

in battle where anything can go wrong its good to have a little luck on your side.

rows.title: Secrets Mission
rows.titleText: secrets missions are events you pick that will happen regardless of what universe you are in, these events allow for lots of points at the cost of a possible world-ending event.

objects.title: innervasion
objects.text:
whenever you transform into Shock Rock,  you will send out a signal to its species the Fulmini, hearing their voices in your head, affecting your sleep, making you try to sleepwalk into creating a way to travel to the world/universe you on, using the Omnitrix. 
if you picked silent guardian, your Omnitrix will do what it can to stop the dreams and sleepwalking caused by the Fulmini, shocking you wake and try to transform you into anything but shock rock unless needed.
Watching Companion is the same but will be able to tell you what happening and may even bring you inside the Omnitrix to battle the Fulmini.

objects.title: The Forever Knights Conspiracy
objects.text: The Forever Knights are a secret society that seeks to eradicate all alien life forms. They possess advanced technology and pose a significant threat to both humans and aliens. they will try to get your omnitrix, you will encounter them in their plot to take over the world

objects.title: The search for the Potis Altiare
objects.text: The Potis Altiare is a device that was created by the ancient Galvan as a device capable of multiplying one's natural abilities several times over, sent away due to its powers is in this universe, whether it be dimensional travel or created by Galvan in this universe, it here, and one day someone will try to get it.

objects.title: Choice
objects.text: You will, regardless of your reputation either receives an invitation or be a plus 1 to a secret gathering of representatives from various alien species across the galaxy. This summit aims to establish peace and cooperation among different civilizations. However, tensions rise as hidden agendas and conflicts emerge. You must navigate through political intrigue, negotiate alliances, and prevent potential conflicts from escalating into full-scale wars.

objects.title: Vilgax attacks
objects.text:
A full-scale invasion by Vilgax, one of Ben's most formidable enemies will happen, you must gather allies, strategize, and engage in intense battles to defend Earth from Vilgax's forces. In this situation, you could always go for a trial of combat to decide Earth's freedom on a one-on-one.

You be facing Alien Force Vilgax with his equipment.

objects.title: Zs'Skayr takeover
objects.text: Zs'Skayr escapes from you Omnitrix, on this new world the scare uses all his resources to become ruler of Earth (or the planet you are on) in the universe. be careful since the scare has read your mind bypassing the Omnitrix defenses, with information on this universe he seeks to rule the universe.

objects.title: interdimensional alien invasion
objects.text: You have an interdimensional alien invasion on your hands, from the Ben 10 universe no less, what will you do during this potentially world-ending threat?

objects.title: Legerdomain
objects.text: Legerdomain, an interdimensional realm believed to be the place from which all magic in the universe flows will be encountered by the world, it will be studied, as people will discover the ability of magic there eventually.

rows.title: The Crossover Begins
rows.titleText:
This section is where the crossover begins, pick which universe you will go to in this endless omniverse which you will venture out.

(more coming)

objects.title: Toaru Raildex
objects.text:
Also known as "A Certain Magical Index," this light novel series is written by Kamachi and set in Academy City, a technologically advanced city that is 30 years ahead of its time. The city focuses on researching and developing espers, individuals endowed with psychic powers that grant them unique abilities using calculations. Don't be deceived, beneath the surface lies the dark side of Academy City where unethical experiments, death, and trafficking are permitted by the corrupt board of directors.

Additionally, there's the Magic side, a hidden realm filled with magic and mysticism. This side is always at odds with the Science side, also known as Academy City, due to their differing worldviews and some interference from Aleister Crowley.

you been sent to academy city if you picked this one, but don't worry, with people like Index and magicians easily walking into the city and out your appearance won't gather any significant interest at first

(in progress)

objects.title: Doctor Who
objects.text:
Welcome to the Doctor Who universe, where Time Lords, Daleks, and Weeping Angels exist, alongside eldritch monstrosities. 

Expect time travel paradoxes, time rifts, and occasional wibbly-wobbly timey-wimey situations.


(in progress)

objects.title: Nasuverse
objects.text:
The Nasuverse is a collection of fantasy works by Nasu Kinoko, ranging from visual novels, games, and light novels, all of which occur within the same multiverse.

(in progress)

objects.title: Marvel
objects.text: welcome to the best superhero comic franchise (Fight Me!) where big names like Ironman, hulk, Captain America, and Spider-Man are at. (in progress)

objects.title: DC
objects.text: Dc universe, gods among man, and all that... yeah I don't have much to say about this one. (in progress)

objects.title: Star Trek
objects.text: years into the future humanity now is a thriving interstellar civilization where men visit other planets and explore where no man or woman has ever set foot on. (in progress)

objects.title: My Hero Academia
objects.text: Welcome to My Hero academia, where most of the population has a quirk also known as a superpower, now you are in a world where even the slightest misuse of your Quirk (Wink Wink) can cost you jail time.    (in progress)

objects.title: Neon Genesis Evangelion
objects.text: Neon Genesis Evangelion takes place in a post-apocalyptic world where giant creatures called Angels threaten humanity's existence. The series follows Shinji Ikari as he is forced to pilot a giant robot known as an Evangelion to protect humanity. (in progress)

objects.title: Once Punch Man
objects.text: revolves around Saitama, a superhero who can defeat any opponent with just one punch. Despite his incredible power, Saitama struggles with boredom and finding worthy opponents.  (in progress)

objects.title: Attack on Titan
objects.text: Based on the manga series by Hajime Isayama, Attack on Titan is set in a world where humanity is on the brink of extinction due to giant humanoid creatures known as Titans. The story follows Eren Yeager and his friends as they join the fight against the Titans and uncover dark secrets about their own existence. (in progress)

objects.title: Steins;Gate
objects.text: This time-travel thriller centers around Rintarou Okabe, a self-proclaimed mad scientist who accidentally discovers the ability to send text messages into the past. As Okabe and his friends experiment with time travel, they become entangled in a conspiracy that could alter the course of history. (in progress)

objects.title: Psycho-Pass
objects.text: In a dystopian future where society is governed by an advanced system called Sybil, Psycho-Pass explores the concept of criminal intent through psychological assessments known as "Psycho-Passes." The story follows Akane Tsunemori, a young inspector who must navigate the complexities of a system that claims to maintain order but may be flawed. (in progress)

rows.title: Raildex companions
rows.titleText:
Your friends that you will meet... or at the very least the people who you will surely encounter.
Picking Isekai will make sure you will encounter each chosen character and ensure that you two somehow hit it off by putting you in a situation where you can be friends.
Picking reincarnation lets your companions, be longtime friends you meet as early as kindergarten.
picking this will change the canon for example picking both Touma and Misaka will alter canon into the two possibly meeting long before their canon encounter through you.

objects.title: Misaka Mikoto
objects.text:
She is the third ranked Level 5 esper in Academy City, and has been nicknamed Railgun.
She's short-tempered, prideful, has an improper attitude with some slightly violent, despite this, she is friendly and easygoing with a strong sense of justice who will do anything for her friends.

If you picked reincarnation alongside this, Misaka will be your childhood friend since elementary school, as in the past while other kids got out of her way due to her being a protg you instead approached her, helping her out of a lonely childhood.

objects.title: Kamijou Touma
objects.text: Kamijou Touma is the kind of person who acts before thinking. Unable to stand idly by when someone is in trouble, he will go to great lengths to help or protect them. Guided by his instincts, he does what he believes is right and is often labeled as "righteous" by others.

objects.title: Shokuhou Misaki
objects.text: Shokuhou Misaki portrays a playful and childish persona. However, this facade masks a far more cunning nature. Despite her ruthless exterior, she isn't inherently bad and cherishes her friendships greatly.

objects.title: Shirai Kuroko
objects.text: Kuroko is a Level 4 esper and a student at Tokiwadai Middle School, where she also serves as a member of Judgment. She is often seen with her best friend, partner, and roommate, Misaka Mikoto, who is the third-ranked Level 5 esper. Despite living in Academy City for 30 years, she remains unaware of the customs still practiced in present-day Japan.

objects.title: Saten Ruiko
objects.text: Saten is a Level 0 student at Academy City and a close friend and classmate of Uiharu Kazari. She possesses an outgoing and friendly personality, with a fondness for internet rumors and urban legends, which she enjoys sharing with her friends.

objects.title: Uiharu Kazari
objects.text: Uiharu Kazari is a Level 1 student at Academy City, and along with her colleague and friend, Shirai Kuroko, she is a member of the student-led law enforcement organization, Judgment. Uiharu is typically shy and humble, yet always friendly. She exhibits high spirits similar to her friend Saten Ruiko. She confesses that her composure is largely due to a self-imposed "limit". Without this limit, she becomes very energetic and can occasionally be absent-minded.

rows.title: Toaru Miscellaneous
rows.titleText:
This is a Toaru Miscellaneous section of items, abilities, and other things you can do before you go off to Toaru.

(in progress)

requireds.beforeText: Required: Toaru Raildex, and either Crossover in the Omniverse or Isekai into another franchise

objects.title: Electron (NV) Goggles
objects.text: These are night vision goggles that enable the user to see in the dark. Additionally, they provide the capability to visualize various electric or magnetic fluxes.

objects.title: F2000R
objects.text: Despite its robust appearance, the rifle is highly portable. It can be disassembled and conveniently transported in a suitcase. The assault rifle is constructed from laminated plastic rather than steel, lending it an appearance akin to a toy gun - hence its name. The rifle is equipped with infrared technology for target detection and uses electronic control to adjust the bullet's trajectory in real time, thereby maximizing the chances of hitting the target. This feature is especially effective when used in conjunction with Electron (NV) Goggles.

objects.title: Misaka's Sibling
objects.text: You will meet a sister clone of Misaka Mikoto, when or where does not matter, it will happen. play your cards right and you have a good excuse for stopping project level shift and have a loyal companion at your side.

objects.title: Esper
objects.text: You are an Esper now, be it gemstone or not, you now have an ability that going to transfer into all your aliens forms. bad new is you can't no longer do any magic without self harm.

rows.title: Raildex Timeline
rows.titleText: This is a row, and inside of it, you can place choices. On both rows and choices Requirements can be placed, which will block a row from being viewed, or make the player unable to select a choice, depending on either Point-types or the Ids of other choices. Point-types can be made in Features then Manage Points. Hovering over buttons will explain what they do. The Design of the project can be changed in 'Modify Design' at the side navigation bar, and private styling for each row can be turned on in the rows Settings. Default text like this can be turned off in Features -> Manage Defaults.

objects.title: April, one year before first year storyline
objects.text:
1 year before main story, an experiment was conducted using Child Errors to gather data about the Crystallized Esper Essence. The experiment was successful, but it resulted in the children falling into a coma. This left Kiyama Harumi, their guardian and teacher, with a strong determination to save them.

In April of the same year, Tsuchimikado Motoharu graduated from middle school and entered Academy City as a spy for the Church. To fully deceive Academy City, he decided to adopt a young girl as his sister. However, his cover was quickly blown and he was discovered to be a spy. Consequently, he was forced to become a multi-agent to ensure his survival. He later enrolls in the Power Curriculum Program, becoming an esper. However, this makes his magic dangerous to use as it could put his life at risk. 

Misaka Mikoto achieves Level 5 shortly after beginning her education at Tokiwadai Middle School. Following the departure of her arrogant roommate, Kessai Kiyoshi moves in. She is assigned by her group to monitor the new Level 5.

objects.title: May, one year before first year storyline
objects.text: Misaka Mikoto meets Shokuhou Misaki before the switch to summer uniforms. Still traumatized from the events involving Dolly, Shokuhou gets off on a bad start with Mikoto, expressing her desire not to see her again. A week later, after the uniform switch, they cross paths once more and engage in an argument, observed by Kessai Kiyoshi. Sha Danshan also encounters Shirai Kuroko. Meanwhile, a conflict between the Mikagami Clique and the Hasekura Clique is orchestrated by a third party during Hasekura Reiri's absence in Paris for a demonstration. In midsummer, L.S.S. and its leader, Matsuo Ryuusuke, pursue Mitsuari Ayu for her abilities. This results in Kamijou Touma encountering both Mitsuari Ayu and Kumokawa Seria. Seria then aids Touma in his efforts to protect Mitsuari.

objects.title: August, one year before first year story arc
objects.text: Throughout the summer, Touma and Misaki frequently crossed paths. This period, particularly August, was later considered by Shokuhou as the happiest time of her life. However, their encounters reached a climax when they were attacked by Deadlock, who were targeting Misaki. In the ensuing conflict, Touma sustained severe injuries. To alleviate his pain while emergency medical technicians administered aid, Misaki utilized her abilities. Unfortunately, this resulted in Touma losing his ability to remember her.

objects.title: Autumn, one year before first year story arc
objects.text:
Shirai Kuroko encounters Uiharu Kazari at the Judgment Training Center. Subsequently, Shirai Kuroko, Konori Mii, and Uiharu Kazari inadvertently become involved in a post office robbery.
BTW, change this event and Kuroko may or may not like you instead of Misaka.

objects.title: Fourth Week of April in Main Story Year 1
objects.text: Shirai Kuroko enrolls into Tokiwadai Middle School and meets Misaka Mikoto.

objects.title: Main Story Year 1: May 11
objects.text: Misaka 9982 is produced.

objects.title: Main Story Year 1: June 17
objects.text: Mikoto first encounters Kamijou Touma when he attempts to rescue her from some delinquents, inadvertently provoking her anger. Following this incident, Mikoto crosses paths with Touma on several occasions, each time attempting to engage him in combat.

objects.title: Main Story Year 1: June 17
objects.text: Mikoto first encounters Kamijou Touma when he attempts to rescue her from some delinquents, inadvertently provoking her anger. Following this incident, Mikoto crosses paths with Touma on several occasions, each time attempting to engage him in combat.

objects.title: Main Story Year 1: June 23
objects.text:
June 23
Kuroko becomes roommates with Mikoto after forcing her previous roommate to move.

objects.title: Main Story Year 1: July 1
objects.text:
Misaka Mikoto goes to Russia for a demonstration for Academy City's partners, and later gets involved with New Light.

If you picked this one, then you automatically get a ticket to Russia for Misaka's demonstration.

objects.title: Main Story Year 1: July 11 (One Week Before July 18) The first of the Graviton bombings begins.
objects.text: The first of the Graviton bombings begins.

objects.title: Main Story Year 1: July 16 (Level Upper Arc)
objects.text:
The Level Upper Arc begins.

Shirai Kuroko, Uiharu Kazari, and Misaka Mikoto respond to a robbery initiated by a group of robbers led by a Level 3 Pyrokinesist.

rows.title: Nasuverse
rows.titleText:
this section shows you the many universes in the Nasuverse that you can choose. Picking more than one mixing both universes into one canon universe, and have fun mixing and matching if you want.

if you picked Anodite then you have an unlimited supply of energy for servants and can draw more mana from the earth.

defaultRowText: This is a row, and inside of it, you can place choices. On both rows and choices Requirements can be placed, which will block a row from being viewed, or make the player unable to select a choice, depending on either Point-types or the Ids of other choices. Point-types can be made in Features then Manage Points. Hovering over buttons will explain what they do. The Design of the project can be changed in 'Modify Design' at the side navigation bar, and private styling for each row can be turned on in the rows Settings. Default text like this can be turned off in Features -> Manage Defaults.
defaultChoiceText: This is a Choice, and inside of it, you can place images and text. Scores can be added to it, and have Point-types attached. Addons can be added underneath the image and text. In the Functions at the bottom of the choice, there is an array of different things that can be done. Default text like this can be turned off in Features then Manage Defaults.
